AzureBlade thought for a moment, She was more lost than him when he 
first came online.

AzureBlade: I see. (He starts flying) It could be a problem either 
with your memory chips or your spark. As I said, we have some fine 
engineers at the base who can help you.

He takes on some speed, flying out of the forest, but not too fast so 
he does not lose her.

--- In nbwrpg@y..., HanaKirei85@a... wrote:
> <<> Still smiling at her, he took flight. His metal, jet-like wings 
made 
> > him soar through the sky. Heading high up, he took some time to 
feel 
> > the wind on his face. After staying still in the sky for a moment, 
he 
> > came back down fast. He broke his fall near the treetops. Finding 
> > Mistra again, he decided to ask some questions. The emotions he 
felt 
> > in her motivated him to continue.
> > 
> > AzureBlade: Mistra! Over here! (he came down lower, but was still 
in 
> > middair) Can I ask you something? What do you remember about 
yourself?>>
> 
> "Hmmm..." Mistra thought as she pumped her own wings, lifting 
herself into 
> the air nearby Azure. What DID she remember...? Her eyes closed for 
a moment 
> in thought as she tried to recover some sort of memory..anything. A 
moment 
> later she quietly sighed, ears back just slightly as she shook her 
head "It's 
> as if...when I woke up on this planet, I'd just woken up in the 
morning. A 
> dream you know you've had...but what exactly it was is just out of 
your 
> reach..."
